Okay. Okay. Okay. Woah.

(Breathe, Ashley).

I just found out that the LSO, the London Symphony Orchestra, is going to be having a bunch of concerts in Florida once again. I REEEEEALLY want to go see them. On July 27, they are playing Beethoven symphonies 1 and 9 in Tampa. This is some of the best music ever written played by (arguably) the best orchestra in the world. You'd have to be crazy to intentionally miss this.

They are playing other concerts, too, but this is the one I really want to see. When else will you have a chance to see Beethoven 9 performed live (by LSO at that)?

SO...who wants to go with me?

Seriously....comment if you're interested.
